FieldFlow Bug Report: Two Critical Issues
Executive Summary
After comprehensive analysis of the codebase, database schema, and chat history, I've identified the root causes of both issues. These are distinct problems requiring separate fixes.

ISSUE 1: Chat Bubbles Display Without Text
Symptom
Chat bubbles appear in the mobile app, but the text content is not displayed. User reports seeing "a little picture" attached instead of message text.
Root Cause Analysis
Location: components/job/ChatTab.tsx
The message text rendering is wrapped in a conditional that only renders when message_type === 'text':
tsx{msg.message_type === 'text' && (
  <Text
    style={[
      styles.messageText,
      { color: isCurrentUser ? '#fff' : theme.colors.text },
    ]}
  >
    {msg.message_text}
  </Text>
)}
The Problem: If message_type is null, undefined, or any value other than the exact string 'text', the <Text> component never renders—even if message_text has valid content.
Why This Happens:

The database schema shows message_type has a default of 'text'::text
The insert operation correctly sets message_type: 'text'
BUT: The issue likely occurs when messages are fetched and message_type comes back as undefined or null due to:

A timing issue where the default hasn't been applied
RLS policies modifying query results
A data type mismatch between TypeScript expectations and Postgres output



Proposed Fix
File: components/job/ChatTab.tsx
Replace the conditional rendering with a more defensive approach:
tsx// BEFORE (problematic):
{msg.message_type === 'text' && (
  <Text ...>{msg.message_text}</Text>
)}

// AFTER (fix):
{msg.message_text && (
  <Text
    style={[
      styles.messageText,
      { color: isCurrentUser ? '#fff' : theme.colors.text },
    ]}
  >
    {msg.message_text}
  </Text>
)}
Alternative (if you want to preserve type checking):
tsx{(msg.message_type === 'text' || msg.message_type === undefined || msg.message_type === null) && msg.message_text && (
  <Text ...>{msg.message_text}</Text>
)}
Additional Debugging Step
Add console logging to verify what's being returned:
tsx// In the messages.map() callback, add:
console.log('Message data:', { 
  id: msg.id, 
  message_type: msg.message_type, 
  message_text: msg.message_text?.substring(0, 20) 
});
```

---

Perfect! I can see the issue clearly. In the `ChatTab.tsx` file, on line 337, the message text is only rendered when `msg.message_type === 'text'`:

```tsx
{msg.message_type === 'text' && (
  <Text
    style={[
      styles.messageText,
      { color: isCurrentUser ? '#fff' : theme.colors.text },
    ]}
  >
    {msg.message_text}
  </Text>
)}
```

If `message_type` is `null`, `undefined`, or any value other than the exact string `'text'`, the text won't render even if `message_text` has valid content.

I'll implement the fix by making the conditional rendering more defensive. I'll also add console logging to help debug what's being returned from the database.

